As shown by Sen, in the absence of flux,
it is always possible to deform such
an F-theory model to a locus in moduli space where it can be thought
of as an orientifold of a IIB Calabi-Yau compactification.
For this reason, we will use the language of IIB orientifolds,
with  being the Calabi-Yau threefold which is orientifolded.
In this language, the term  counts the negative
D3-brane charge coming from the  planes and the induced D3
charge on  branes, while the terms on the right-hand side
count the net D3 charge from transverse branes and fluxes in
the CY manifold.
