having only one Kahler modulus, so 
(, and one modulus is frozen in taking the
F-theory limit, where one shrinks the elliptic fiber).  Such models
can be explicitly constructed, by e.g. using the examples
of CY fourfolds in or by explicitly constructing
orientifolds of known CY threefolds with .

