Coleman-De Luccia (CDL) instantons are more complicated.  They describe the field  beginning in a vicinity of the false vacuum
 at ,  and reaching some constant value  at , where . It is tempting to interpret CDL instantons as the tunneling trajectories interpolating between the different vacua of the theory. However, one should be careful with this interpretation because the trajectories  for CDL instantons do not  begin exactly in the 
metastable minimum  and do not  end exactly in the absolute minimum of the effective potential. We will discuss this issue later.

